    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="195"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <head>195. Information Report Prepared in the Central Intelligence Agency<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d195fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency, <gloss
                            target="#t_DDI_1">DDI</gloss> Files, Job 80–00810A, Box 11, Folder 27,
                        CS Information Reports 8550–8559. Secret; Security Information; Control—U.S.
                        Officials Only.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <idno type="document-identifier">CS–8550</idno>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-04-24"
                        >April 24, 1953</date>.</dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Activities of Anti-<persName corresp="#p_MM_1">Mossadeq</persName>
                        Groups</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <head>SOURCE</head>
                    <item>[<hi rend="italic">2 lines not declassified</hi>]</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. The opposition to <persName corresp="#p_MM_1">Mossadeq</persName> was “greatly
                    discouraged” by the American Embassy’s statement regarding the Shiraz
                        incident,<note n="2" xml:id="d195fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington Comment.</hi> On 20 April the American Embassy
                        in Tehran issued a press statement to the effect that United States policy
                        toward Iran has not changed as a result of the Shiraz incident. [Footnote is
                        in the original.]</note> but is continuing its efforts to unseat the Prime
                    Minister.</p>
                <p>2. The Shah promised “two weeks ago” to give financial aid to General <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZA_1">Fazullah Zahedi</persName> but to date no aid has been
                    received.</p>
                <p>3. Dr. Mossafar Baghai has joined <persName corresp="#p_ZA_1">Zahedi</persName>
                    against <persName corresp="#p_MM_1">Mossadeq</persName>.</p>
            </div>
